{"id":"1589","name":"Low Power","tagline":"Quickly turn on Low Power Mode and turn off WiFi and Bluetooth","icon":"ios13 c4274264319 g59782","latest":"11261","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>This shortcut turns on low power mode and turns off WiFi and Bluetooth. It is very useful when you are trying to charge your phone as quickly as possible.</p>\n<p>It doesn't effect your ability to make or receive calls or receive or send messages via text (cellular data).</p>\n<p>It can even be run from your Apple Watch to make these settings on your phone! It doesn't effect the Watch settings so you can still use it over WiFi or cellular.</p>\n<p>This shortcut can be run stand-alone or from another shortcut such as <em>RoutineKit</em> or <em>My RoutineKit</em> which will pull information from various other shortcuts like this together.</p>\n<p>This shortcut incorporates the <em>UpdateKit</em> shortcut so users can receive a notification to download a new version when updates are available.</p>\n<p><em>Keywords: low power, charging, WiFi, Bluetooth, RoutineKit.</em></p>\n<p><em>Supports: RoutineKit, UpdateKit.</em></p>\n<p><em>Compatibility: iPhone, iPad, Apple Watch and HomePod (changes iPhone settings).</em></p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.3 - Oct. 6, 2019, 7:07 p.m.</strong></p><p>Fix for UpdateKit with iOS 13. Also added an option to display the results in a notification instead of an alert when called from RoutineKit.</p>"}